                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">From the legation of H. L. M. the Shah of Persia, at Paris, to
                        the United States Minister</hi>.</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-09">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 9, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>I have just received a telegram from Teheran, expressive of the horror felt by
                    the government of his imperial Majesty the Shah of Persia at the news of the
                    assassination of Mr. Lincoln.</p>
                <p>I am requested by him to express to you his great regrets on this occasion, and
                    to ask you to transmit them to your new President. Accept the assurance of my
                    very high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SULEYMAN RHAN,</signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Persian Chargé d’Affaires</hi>.</closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>His Excellency Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Bigelow</hi>, <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States Envoy and Minister Plenipotentiary, &amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
